{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BcinorH8dWESR5EfoWKZjD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\"\"\"Integration test for gl_cuda_interop.py.\n     2→\n     3→Creates an OpenGL VBO of 1 M float4s, registers it with CUDA via the\n     4→ctypes wrapper, writes a grid pattern using a CuPy RawKernel, then\n     5→draws the points with glDrawArrays(GL_POINTS) and verifies no errors.\n     6→\n     7→Requirements: glfw, PyOpenGL, cupy, numpy, an NVIDIA GPU with CUDA 12.x.\n     8→\"\"\"\n     9→\n    10→from __future__ import annotations\n    11→\n    12→import ctypes\n    13→import sys\n    14→import numpy as np\n    15→\n    16→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    17→# GLFW / OpenGL bootstrap\n    18→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    19→\n    20→import glfw\n    21→from OpenGL.GL import (\n    22→    GL_ARRAY_BUFFER,\n    23→    GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT,\n    24→    GL_DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT,\n    25→    GL_DYNAMIC_DRAW,\n    26→    GL_FLOAT,\n    27→    GL_NO_ERROR,\n    28→    GL_POINTS,\n    29→    glBindBuffer,\n    30→    glBufferData,\n    31→    glClear,\n    32→    glClearColor,\n    33→    glDrawArrays,\n    34→    glEnableVertexAttribArray,\n    35→    glGenBuffers,\n    36→    glGetError,\n    37→    glPointSize,\n    38→    glVertexAttribPointer,\n    39→    glViewport,\n    40→)\n    41→\n    42→import cupy\n    43→import cupy.cuda.compiler as _compiler\n    44→from gl_cuda_interop import CudaGLBuffer, check_last_error\n    45→\n    46→# Blackwell (sm_120) PTX workaround: force PTX output so the driver JIT-compiles\n    47→_compiler._use_ptx = True\n    48→for _fn in (_compiler._get_arch, _compiler._get_arch_for_options_for_nvrtc):\n    49→    if hasattr(_fn, '_cache'):\n    50→        _fn._cache = {}\n    51→\n    52→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    53→# Constants\n    54→# --------